name: Chikorita
flavorText: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.
Attack2Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Bayleef
flavorText: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Meganium
flavorText: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon's remaining HP is 50 or less, its attacks do 70 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Seedot
flavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

name: Kricketot
flavorText: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Grass Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Kricketune
flavorText: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, any damage done to the Defending Pokémon by attacks is increased by 60 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Petilil
flavorText: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

name: Lilligant
flavorText: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.
Attack1Text: If your opponent attaches an Energy card from his or her hand to the Defending Pokémon during his or her next turn, that Pokémon will be Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Durant
flavorText: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, discard the top 4 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can't help but grovel before it.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Numel
flavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

name: Camerupt
flavorText: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
Attack2Text: Each player discards the top card of his or her deck. This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy card discarded in this way.

name: Emboar-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

name: Golduck
flavorText: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Golduck BREAK
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a basic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won't even notice for a whole day.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Slowbro
flavorText: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: If you use this attack when you have only 1 Prize card left, you win this game.

name: Slowking
flavorText: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke's head and unlocked an extraordinary power.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Psych Up attack does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Shellder
flavorText: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Shellder
flavorText: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Cloyster
flavorText: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon evolved from Shellder during this turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Staryu
flavorText: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

name: Gyarados-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: M Gyarados-EX
Attack1Text: You may do 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you do, discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Lapras
flavorText: Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Trainer card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Corsola
flavorText: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Suicune
flavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to each of your Pokémon. (Existing effects are not removed.)

name: Palkia-EX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 Water Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Manaphy-EX
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Water Energy attached to it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Tympole
flavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage times the number of your Pokémon in play that have the Round attack.

name: Palpitoad
flavorText: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Seismitoad
flavorText: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.
Attack1Text: Attach 3 Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. That Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Frogadier
flavorText: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Frogadier and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Greninja
flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
Attack1Text: Until the end of your opponent's next turn, each Pokémon your opponent has in play, in his or her hand, and in his or her discard pile has no Abilities. (This includes cards that come into play on that turn.)
Attack2Text: You may return a Water Energy from this Pokémon to your hand. If you do, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Greninja BREAK
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may discard a Water Energy card from your hand. If you do, put 6 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.

name: Electivire
flavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: Shinx
flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

name: Luxio
flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Luxray
flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Luxray BREAK
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Ability1Text: Damage from the attacks of your Lightning Pokémon isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has Fighting Resistance, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Hypno
flavorText: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may leave both Active Pokémon Asleep.

name: Espeon-EX
Attack1Text: Devolve each of your opponent's evolved Pokémon and put the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Skorupi
flavorText: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Drapion
flavorText: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 5 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals his or her hand.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, each Pokémon in play, in each player's hand, and in each player's discard pile has no Abilities (except for Garbotoxin).
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Espurr
flavorText: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

name: Meowstic
flavorText: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Energy cards from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Honedge
flavorText: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Doublade
flavorText: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Apparently, it can detect innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
Attack1Text: Double the number of damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Skrelp
flavorText: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Phantump
flavorText: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon. (This counts as evolving this Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Trevenant
flavorText: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Basic Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless more.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Trevenant BREAK
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Sudowoodo
flavorText: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Pokémon used an attack during his or her last turn, use it as this attack.

name: Gible
flavorText: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 2 cards.

name: Gabite
flavorText: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Garchomp
flavorText: It flies at speeds equals to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon-EX, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Pancham
flavorText: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If any of them are heads, your opponent reveals his or her hand. Then, for each heads, discard a card from your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: Put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Darkrai-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Asleep, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Pangoro
flavorText: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 60 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Scizor-EX
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: M Scizor-EX
Attack1Text: You may discard a Special Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon or a Stadium card in play.

name: Mawile
flavorText: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokémon if that damage is 60 or less.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon for each Colorless in that Pokémon's Retreat Cost. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Clefairy
flavorText: The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by Dragon Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Togekiss-EX
Attack1Text: You may attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Spritzee
flavorText: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

name: Aromatisse
flavorText: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon-EX, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Dragalge
flavorText: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 4 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.
Attack2Text: Discard the top card of your deck.

name: Rattata
flavorText: Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.
Attack1Text: Draw a card. Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Raticate
flavorText: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It searches wide areas for food.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can't be affected by any Special Conditions. (Remove any Special Conditions affecting this Pokémon.)
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Discard all Pokémon Tool cards attached to that Pokémon.

name: Raticate BREAK
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

name: Dunsparce
flavorText: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Stantler
flavorText: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you have any Mega Evolution Pokémon on your Bench, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Ho-Oh-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon has any basic Fire Energy attached to it, you may heal 50 damage from it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon).

name: Glameow
flavorText: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent puts a card from his or her hand on the bottom of his or her deck.

name: Purugly
flavorText: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Furfrou
flavorText: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Gyarados-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: M Gyarados-EX
Attack1Text: You may do 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you do, discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Manaphy-EX
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Water Energy attached to it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Espeon-EX
Attack1Text: Devolve each of your opponent's evolved Pokémon and put the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Darkrai-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Asleep, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Scizor-EX
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: M Scizor-EX
Attack1Text: You may discard a Special Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon or a Stadium card in play.

name: Ho-Oh-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon has any basic Fire Energy attached to it, you may heal 50 damage from it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Gyarados-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
